<li id="cite_note-21"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">T. Watt, <i>Cheap Print and Popular Piety, 1550-1640</i> (Cambridge University Press, 1991), p. 11.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">M. Spufford, <i>Small Books and Pleasant Histories: Popular Fiction and Its Readership in Seventeenth-Century England</i> (Cambridge University Press, 1985), pp. 111-28.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">B. Capp, ‘Popular literature’, in B. Reay, ed., <i>Popular Culture in Seventeenth-Century England</i> (Routledge, 1985), p. 204.</span></li>
